115. Cresphonte: Cresphontes is the name of a tragedy of Euripides, of which only a few fragments remain. The hero, Cres- phontes, one of the Heraclidae and king of Messenia, was slain with his two sons by the nobles, because he favored the people. For the original of the passage here translated, cf.
